    &lt;ScreenName&gt;Helen&lt;/ScreenName&gt;
    &lt;CommentText&gt;i was on ward 32 at tameside hospital had no complaints about doctors nurses and health assistant cleaning was very good always made sure that our side ward was kept clean but what drove me crazy was the number of time the call buzzer was being used and they were always on the go day and night for long periods of time up to 30-45mins before it’s turned off and as soon as that buzzer is turned of then another one starts when your in a lot of pain and not feeling very well the last thing you want is buzzers being left on for long periods of time what I cannot understand is why can’t you have flashing lights instead of buzzers like in the old days whenever people require attention this would not disturb other patients the buzzers which are very loud made me want to leave hospital early but I was told that I needed to stay in until I was well enough to leave even when I told the nurses about the buzzers driving me crazy there was peace for about 10 minutes before the buzzers started again even now I am out of hospital I can still hear the buzzers going off in my head it’s sad really you go into hospital to get better not to get a nervous breakdown for all the time I was in there I never slept my body wanted to sleep but I just couldn’t sleep&lt;/CommentText&gt;
